From: PS3 Custom Toolchain
Subject: [PATCH] elf64-ppc: skip OPD optimisation for compact 8-byte .opd

CellOS Lv-2 uses a compact 8-byte function-descriptor format in
.opd ([entry_ea_32, toc_ea_32] with R_PPC64_ADDR32 relocs at
offsets 0 and 4).  ppc64_elf_edit_opd() assumes the standard
PPC64 ELFv1 24-byte three-doubleword layout with
R_PPC64_ADDR64+R_PPC64_TOC pairs at offsets 0 and 8, and emits
".opd is not a regular array of opd entries" when the compact
layout is present.

Skip the OPD optimisation pass for compact .opd sections,
detected by the section alignment_power: ELFv1 .opd uses
alignment 8 (power=3), compact .opd uses alignment 4 (power=2).
Compact .opd sections are much smaller than ELFv1 ones, so the
lost optimisation is not material.

--- a/bfd/elf64-ppc.c
+++ b/bfd/elf64-ppc.c
@@ -7400,6 +7400,18 @@
       if (sec->output_section == bfd_abs_section_ptr)
 	continue;
 
+      /* CellOS Lv-2 uses a compact 8-byte .opd layout
+	 [entry_ea_32, toc_ea_32] with 4-byte alignment and only
+	 R_PPC64_ADDR32 relocations -- incompatible with the
+	 24-byte ELFv1 layout this pass assumes.  Detected via
+	 alignment power: ELFv1 .opd uses 8-byte alignment
+	 (power=3); compact .opd uses 4-byte (power=2).  Skip
+	 OPD optimisation entirely for compact sections; they
+	 are small enough that the lost optimisation does not
+	 matter.  */
+      if (sec->alignment_power < 3)
+	continue;
+
       /* Look through the section relocs.  */
       if ((sec->flags & SEC_RELOC) == 0 || sec->reloc_count == 0)
 	continue;
